data.content:
Create `.vscode/mcp.json` with this content:

```json
{
  "servers": {
    "MyMcpServer": {
      "type": "stdio",
      "command": "dotnet",
      "args": ["run", "--project", "src/MyMcpServer/MyMcpServer.csproj"]
    }
  }
}
```

> If your server uses **HTTP transport** (has a `ModelContextProtocol.AspNetCore` package reference), use this instead:
> ```json
> {
>   "servers": {
>     "MyMcpServer": {
>       "type": "http",
>       "url": "http://localhost:3001"
>     }
>   }
> }
> ```

**To verify it works:**
1. Open Copilot Chat → switch to **Agent** mode
2. Click the **wrench icon** (Select Tools) → confirm your tools are listed
3. Ask a prompt that triggers one of your tools

**If tools don't appear**, rebuild first (`dotnet build`), restart the MCP server in VS Code, and ensure your tool classes have `[McpServerToolType]` and methods have `[McpServerTool]`.
